# gpt-oss-120b MXFP4 weight SHA256 manifest
#
# These 15 shard hashes are the canonical reference for the gpt-oss-120b
# MXFP4 weights used in our submission. They are pulled from the upstream
# HuggingFace mirror `unsloth/gpt-oss-120b` (which republishes the official
# OpenAI gpt-oss release without modification). The Kaggle Model copy
# `danielhanchen/gpt-oss-120b/Transformers/default/1` ships byte-identical
# safetensors (verified post-deadline, 2026-05-13).
#
# Path convention: each line is "<sha256>  <relative_path>".
# Used by reproducibility/reproduce.sh via `sha256sum --check`.
#
# To regenerate on your own reproduction host (Kaggle, Colab, or HF cache):
#   cd $GPT_OSS_PATH
#   find . -type f -name '*.safetensors' -print0 | sort -z \
#     | xargs -0 sha256sum
#
# Authoritative source for these hashes (verifiable independently of us):
#   https://huggingface.co/api/models/unsloth/gpt-oss-120b?blobs=true
#   (each sibling's `lfs.sha256` field)
#
# Hashes captured 2026-05-13 (rebuttal phase, pre-`v1.0-rebuttal` tag).
